BorgWarner: A Resilient Player in the Motor Vehicles & Parts Sector

In the 2024 Fortune ranking, BorgWarner, a prominent player in the Motor Vehicles & Parts sector, secured the 258th position, marking a notable improvement in its standing. With a modest 4.0 point gain in rank, the company demonstrated its ability to navigate the complex and competitive landscape of the industry.

Founded by a visionary entrepreneur, BorgWarner is now led by Frederic B. Lissalde, who has been instrumental in steering the company towards sustained growth and profitability. As a testament to its financial health, BorgWarner has consistently reported profits, reinforcing its position as a reliable player in the market.

Headquartered in Auburn Hills, Michigan, BorgWarner boasts a significant global presence, with a workforce of approximately 39,900 employees. The company's commitment to innovation and quality has earned it a spot in the esteemed list of the World's Most Admired Companies, a distinction that underscores its dedication to excellence.

BorgWarner's financial performance in the latest reported period reflects a revenue of $15,921 million, representing a modest growth of 0.8% over the previous period. While the company's profits declined by 33.8% to $625 million, its overall financial health remains robust, with total assets valued at $14,453 million as of the latest reporting period.

The company's market capitalization, as of March 28, 2024, stood at $8,023.4 million, underscoring its position as a major player in the industry. BorgWarner's publicly traded status and listing on the stock exchange under the ticker symbol BWA provide investors with a viable opportunity to participate in the company's growth and success.

BorgWarner's resilience in the face of industry challenges is a testament to its ability to adapt and evolve. As the company continues to navigate the complexities of the Motor Vehicles & Parts sector, its commitment to innovation, quality, and customer satisfaction is likely to drive its growth and success in the years to come.

For more information about BorgWarner, please visit the company's website at https://www.borgwarner.com.